{"id":"08ce984a-4628-416d-b4ee-a1641234c8dd","title":"1557/05: To the Most Illustrious Lord Cosimo, Duke of Florence","type":"main-list-block","children":[{"id":"ad47e54e-404c-4713-bde9-cebb810a1326","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"From Rome, [May ..., 1557].","standoffProperties":[{"id":"f9d15a37-5fa4-4d9b-b437-b4811927442a","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":5,"end":8,"value":"501a8a32-2c8a-4934-9060-8c7e36339f0f","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"f28df4f1-c935-42b2-bcb5-5808b9a34fdc","type":"tei/core/date","start":12,"end":24,"value":null,"zeroPoint":false,"metadata":["when|1557-05"]},{"id":"2b34c213-284a-4304-ab52-062f9f153328","type":"codex/time-reference","start":12,"end":24,"value":"d558f552-4bb5-4609-a2c6-992af4901fb7","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]}],"blockProperties":[]},{"id":"329f398c-7882-482b-9c43-b8ff8a1adcab","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"To the Most Illustrious Lord Cosimo, Duke of Florence.","standoffProperties":[{"id":"5d8ee71c-3b90-492b-ab55-0f94caa88f09","type":"tei/textstructure/salute","start":0,"end":53,"value":null,"zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"ec437ada-9765-482b-877f-8f65af479331","type":"style/italics","start":0,"end":52,"value":null,"zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"74a44bbd-1c18-488f-a4ec-84b76cc300b0","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":24,"end":34,"value":"ac52a90a-3e3e-4c05-ace5-5b6da5a37fec","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"9c00f095-41f3-4894-ab10-aad115d3b20e","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":37,"end":52,"value":"ac52a90a-3e3e-4c05-ace5-5b6da5a37fec","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]}],"blockProperties":[{"id":"5d8ee71c-3b90-492b-ab55-0f94caa88f09","type":"tei/textstructure/salute","value":null,"metadata":[]}]},{"id":"8df968fd-f63e-4f2b-a009-2b74a89b1aef","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"My Lord Duke,\u00A0\u2014\u00A0About three months ago, or rather less, I caused Your Lordship to be informed\u00A0that I could not desert the fabric of St. Peter\u0027s without exposing it to great risks and without the very\u00A0greatest dishonour to myself: and I said also that,\u00A0supposing I could obtain all the necessary material,\u00A0I should require to devote at least another year to\u00A0the work before I could bring it to the condition in\u00A0which I should wish to leave it. I asked that I\u00A0might be excused for this period, and said I thought Your Lordship would be content to grant my request. I have now received a letter from Your Lordship, however, which urges me to return sooner than I had expected; and for that reason I am not a little\u00A0troubled, as I find myself at this present time face to face with a more difficult and intricate problem\u00A0than any I have hitherto encountered in respect to\u00A0the building. I refer to the vaulting in the King of\u00A0France\u0027s chapel, a very difficult and unusual piece of construction where some error has arisen through my being an old man and unable to inspect the work at very frequent intervals. To correct this I am compelled to pull down most of what has already been executed. Bastiano da San Gimignano, who was in\u00A0charge of the work here, will be able to explain the\u00A0nature of this chapel as well as the important part it\u00A0plays in the whole construction. Once this chapel has been put right I think the remainder of the work\u00A0could be finished by the end of this summer, so that all I should have to do would be to leave them the\u00A0model for the whole work, as I have been asked to\u00A0do by everyone, especially by [the Cardinal Rodolfo Pio da] Carpi. Then I should be free to return to\u00A0Florence with the one thought of preparing to meet death, with whom day and night I am trying to make friends so that at the end he may not treat me worse\u00A0than other old folk.","standoffProperties":[{"id":"3f0d4118-650c-4ae1-abab-3a72a337805e","type":"tei/textstructure/salute","start":0,"end":11,"value":null,"zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"4a08a936-d8c5-44c1-8